265
00:21:47,869 --> 00:21:48,912
You don't remember?

266
00:21:49,829 --> 00:21:50,830
No.

267
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,252
I remember getting hit really hard once.

268
00:21:57,503 --> 00:21:59,088
After that one big hit...

269
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:03,509
What happened?

270
00:22:07,639 --> 00:22:10,224
My whole body is aching.
Did I get beat up badly?

271
00:22:11,476 --> 00:22:12,602
Uncle.

272
00:22:12,936 --> 00:22:15,063
Getting beat up
isn't what matters right now.

273
00:22:16,606 --> 00:22:17,690
But, why are you...

274
00:22:19,233 --> 00:22:20,568
calling me "Uncle"?

275
00:22:21,694 --> 00:22:23,279
Not "Hey, you" like before.

276
00:22:24,948 --> 00:22:28,618
Oh, that's because I didn't really know
you back then.

277
00:22:30,203 --> 00:22:33,373
I'm telling you, it was like
watching a martial arts movie.

278
00:22:33,623 --> 00:22:35,833
- You're saying that's me?
- Yeah!

279
00:22:36,459 --> 00:22:38,252
All of a sudden, you just snapped.

280
00:22:38,336 --> 00:22:39,337
You were, like...

281
00:22:41,172 --> 00:22:42,340
And after a few moves

282
00:22:42,423 --> 00:22:43,841
you just wiped the floor with them.

283
00:22:45,843 --> 00:22:47,011
I don't remember any of that.

284
00:22:49,263 --> 00:22:51,724
Are you sure you're not lying to cover up
something you did?

285
00:22:52,058 --> 00:22:53,142
Come on

286
00:22:53,226 --> 00:22:55,353
why would I make something like that up?

287
00:22:55,853 --> 00:22:56,980
Watch again. See?

288
00:23:02,318 --> 00:23:03,319
How can that be me?

289
00:23:03,403 --> 00:23:05,071
I think when things got dangerous

290
00:23:05,154 --> 00:23:07,198
your hidden past must have come out.

291
00:23:08,449 --> 00:23:10,410
- A hidden past?
- Yeah.

292
00:23:10,493 --> 00:23:12,370
You know, like in the movies.

293
00:23:12,578 --> 00:23:14,038
When the hero is in danger

294
00:23:14,122 --> 00:23:17,041
their past just suddenly
comes flashing back.

295
00:23:17,625 --> 00:23:19,752
Anything coming back to you, Uncle?

296
00:23:21,295 --> 00:23:22,588
No, my head just hurts.

297
00:23:24,132 --> 00:23:27,260
So I came up with a theory.

298
00:23:27,719 --> 00:23:29,512
Who are you really, Uncle?

299
00:23:29,971 --> 00:23:31,180
How can you be such a good fighter?

300
00:23:33,141 --> 00:23:34,434
And the answer became obvious.

301
00:23:36,019 --> 00:23:37,103
A 007 agent.

302
00:23:37,979 --> 00:23:39,313
And I never said it

303
00:23:39,397 --> 00:23:40,982
but I always thought the vibe you give off

304
00:23:41,190 --> 00:23:42,984
was really intense.

305
00:23:45,528 --> 00:23:47,280
I suppose I do have that side to me.

306
00:23:50,616 --> 00:23:52,368
Is it that obvious to you?

307
00:23:53,244 --> 00:23:54,412
Yeah, I'm telling you!

308
00:23:56,622 --> 00:23:57,749
Bulgae showed up!

309
00:23:57,832 --> 00:24:00,460
- It was Bulgae!
- Hey, Ho-myeong, calm down.

310
00:24:00,877 --> 00:24:02,712
Seong-won, run a trace
on a motorcycle plate.

311
00:24:02,795 --> 00:24:05,048
It's Imcheon, Yeongseon-ga

312
00:24:05,256 --> 00:24:06,674
- 9342.
- Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong!

313
00:24:06,758 --> 00:24:08,885
No, on second thought, you get down here.
We'll look for him together.

314
00:24:08,968 --> 00:24:10,887
The more you rush,
the more careful you have to be.

315
00:24:10,970 --> 00:24:12,388
Have you already forgotten
what happened that day, ten years ago?

316
00:24:15,475 --> 00:24:16,476
Ho-myeong

317
00:24:16,559 --> 00:24:18,853
I'll get you the plate search
results by tomorrow morning.

318
00:24:19,145 --> 00:24:20,521
You need to confirm
whether that guy is really Bulgae

319
00:24:20,605 --> 00:24:22,148
and if he actually has the goods.

320
00:24:22,231 --> 00:24:23,983
Focus on that first. All right?

321
00:24:24,192 --> 00:24:26,194
I'll finish up here and be right there.

322
00:24:26,736 --> 00:24:28,279
Okay? Be smart about this.

323
00:24:28,946 --> 00:24:30,281
- All right.
- Okay.

324
00:24:32,575 --> 00:24:35,411
- That Jeong Ho-myeong...
- Hey, mister!

325
00:24:35,995 --> 00:24:37,580
So, when's it going to be ready?

326
00:24:38,122 --> 00:24:39,540
Oh, yes. It'll be right out.

327
00:24:40,541 --> 00:24:42,335
- Good grief.
- I'm sorry.

328
00:24:42,877 --> 00:24:46,214
How long do I have to wait
for just one of these things? Seriously.

329
00:24:50,802 --> 00:24:52,136
Get out.

330
00:24:52,220 --> 00:24:54,263
I'm sorry, boss. I messed up, boss.

331
00:24:54,347 --> 00:24:56,224
- I just...
- Get out.

332
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:01,771
Wait a minute. For real.

333
00:25:01,854 --> 00:25:03,439
Hold still, you bastard,
before you get hurt.

334
00:25:03,564 --> 00:25:05,108
It really hurts. It hurts so much.

335
00:25:05,191 --> 00:25:08,027
And the spot where that guy
hit me earlier still hurts like hell.

336
00:25:08,945 --> 00:25:11,072
You lose all the deeds
we worked so hard to collect

337
00:25:11,155 --> 00:25:12,448
and now you're complaining
that you're in pain?

338
00:25:12,865 --> 00:25:15,201
I'm telling you, he was no ordinary guy.

339
00:25:15,785 --> 00:25:18,746
The way his body was just flying around...

340
00:25:18,830 --> 00:25:20,623
He was like a martial arts master.

341
00:25:20,706 --> 00:25:22,291
And the other guy, the one in the hat...

342
00:25:22,375 --> 00:25:24,335
his hands and feet were unbelievably fast.

343
00:25:24,585 --> 00:25:26,796
It made me wonder what guys like them were
doing in a backwater place like this.

344
00:25:26,879 --> 00:25:28,548
For real.

345
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:31,217
What are you doing,
writing a restaurant review?

346
00:25:32,176 --> 00:25:34,262
- So how many stars?
- A lot... Wait, I'm sorry.

347
00:25:34,804 --> 00:25:36,514
Hey, you goddamn morons!

348
00:25:36,597 --> 00:25:38,141
If you're going to come back after getting
your asses handed to you

349
00:25:38,224 --> 00:25:41,227
you should've at least brought back a
video or a photo of the bastard's face!

350
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:42,979
Come on, you know how it is, Boss.

351
00:25:43,396 --> 00:25:45,273
Our security cameras are just for show.

352
00:25:45,356 --> 00:25:47,275
In case any issues came up later

353
00:25:47,608 --> 00:25:49,944
you're the one who told us not to install
real cameras at the loan office.

354
00:25:50,027 --> 00:25:51,696
Don't you remember ordering that yourself?

355
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,489
Right. So now it's my fault?

356
00:25:54,782 --> 00:25:55,783
- Hold it out.
- Yes, sir.

357
00:25:58,369 --> 00:26:00,121
Wait, that really hurts!

358
00:26:00,204 --> 00:26:01,205
I'm so sorry...

359
00:26:04,250 --> 00:26:05,334
All of you, get up!

360
00:26:05,418 --> 00:26:07,420
Oh, what do I do?

361
00:26:11,841 --> 00:26:12,925
- Hey.
- Yes, sir.

362
00:26:13,467 --> 00:26:15,303
Go sweet-talk the hotel security team

363
00:26:15,386 --> 00:26:16,679
and get the lobby's CCTV footage.

364
00:26:17,388 --> 00:26:18,848
Do it quietly, without Chairman Do
finding out.

365
00:26:19,098 --> 00:26:21,017
Why without Chairman Do finding out?

366
00:26:21,142 --> 00:26:22,977
Hey, you idiot. Can't you think?

367
00:26:23,144 --> 00:26:25,062
Chairman Do is just dying to
get rid of us.

368
00:26:25,146 --> 00:26:26,647
If she finds out this happened

369
00:26:27,356 --> 00:26:28,774
do you think she'd just let us be?

370
00:26:29,025 --> 00:26:31,569
And if word gets out about trouble at one
of our spots, and Chief Han hears about it

371
00:26:31,652 --> 00:26:33,487
- don't you know we're finished?
- Right.

372
00:26:35,281 --> 00:26:36,449
You have three days

373
00:26:36,532 --> 00:26:38,367
to catch those bastards
and drag them here to me.

374
00:26:39,035 --> 00:26:40,369
I don't care if he's a martial arts
master or just some guy in a cap.

375
00:26:40,453 --> 00:26:41,621
I'll kill him myself.

376
00:26:41,871 --> 00:26:42,872
Yes, I understand, Boss.

377
00:26:43,623 --> 00:26:45,082
Answer, you bastards! Damn it.

378
00:26:45,166 --> 00:26:46,209
- Yes, Boss!
- Yes, Boss!

379
00:26:47,001 --> 00:26:48,085
But, Boss...

380
00:26:49,045 --> 00:26:50,046
Where do I find them?

381
00:26:52,882 --> 00:26:54,967
- You want me to put it in your GPS?
- I'm sorry.

382
00:26:55,343 --> 00:26:57,261
What are you waiting for? Go! Now!

383
00:26:57,553 --> 00:26:59,430
Let's go! Come on, let's move!

384
00:26:59,513 --> 00:27:00,514
Damn it!

385
00:27:01,390 --> 00:27:02,391
I'm serious.

386
00:27:02,475 --> 00:27:04,685
The loan sharks were all beaten to a pulp.

387
00:27:06,187 --> 00:27:07,188
So?

388
00:27:07,271 --> 00:27:08,314
What do you mean, so?

389
00:27:08,773 --> 00:27:11,359
This is a guy who hasn't gotten a single
speeding ticket in ten years.

390
00:27:11,442 --> 00:27:13,152
He must've had a reason for making a move.

391
00:27:14,028 --> 00:27:15,488
Let's put him under 24-hour surveillance

392
00:27:15,571 --> 00:27:16,572
and get to the bottom of this.

393
00:27:16,697 --> 00:27:19,033
If you're on 24-hour surveillance,
what about our 24-hour convenience store?

394
00:27:20,201 --> 00:27:21,369
Well, we'll have to close up shop.

395
00:27:21,452 --> 00:27:23,746
That's fine by me.
I was getting sick of this place anyway.

396
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:25,289
Jeez, Gong-bok.

397
00:27:25,581 --> 00:27:27,708
Were you late for your shift

398
00:27:27,792 --> 00:27:28,834
because you were doing this useless stuff?

399
00:27:28,918 --> 00:27:30,503
Who cares about my shift right now?

400
00:27:30,586 --> 00:27:31,837
He's made his move.

401
00:27:31,921 --> 00:27:34,006
The guy we've been watching for ten years.

402
00:27:34,131 --> 00:27:37,218
Our Boss, who was framed and sent to
prison, all our scattered guys...

403
00:27:37,301 --> 00:27:39,929
This could be our one chance to get it all
back. Why are you hesitating?

404
00:27:40,012 --> 00:27:41,847
I'm asking why he would suddenly make a
move now!

405
00:27:41,931 --> 00:27:42,932
There's no reason for it!

406
00:27:43,015 --> 00:27:44,642
That's what I'm saying we should find out.

407
00:27:45,184 --> 00:27:47,144
Come on. You never used to hesitate.
What's wrong?

408
00:27:49,355 --> 00:27:52,650
Oh, I know. It's because of that cop,
isn't it? That lady cop.

409
00:27:54,568 --> 00:27:55,569
What?

410
00:27:57,613 --> 00:27:58,614
Well...

411
00:28:03,327 --> 00:28:05,705
Wow. Unbelievable.

412
00:28:06,163 --> 00:28:07,164
Hey.

413
00:28:07,540 --> 00:28:10,126
In what convenience store does the
part-timer spy on the owner, huh?

414
00:28:12,086 --> 00:28:13,170
What did you just say?

415
00:28:13,296 --> 00:28:14,380
- Part-timer?
- Yep.

416
00:28:15,548 --> 00:28:17,675
- Am I just a part-timer at this store?
- Yeah.

417
00:28:19,593 --> 00:28:21,053
Okay, I see how you really feel.

418
00:28:21,262 --> 00:28:22,263
As for Jeong Ho-myeong

419
00:28:22,346 --> 00:28:25,141
I'll keep a close watch on him by myself.

420
00:28:28,936 --> 00:28:30,938
Go, just go! Fine, go.

421
00:28:31,022 --> 00:28:32,148
Hey, pay for that!

422
00:28:32,606 --> 00:28:34,400
Wait, don't go!
You have to take over for me!

423
00:28:35,318 --> 00:28:37,320
I just pulled an all-nighter!

424
00:29:37,171 --> 00:29:38,339
Nice shot.

425
00:29:45,596 --> 00:29:46,639
CONVERTING TO MULTIMEDIA MESSAGE...

426
00:29:50,309 --> 00:29:53,437
Yes, Chief Kim. I just sent you a license
plate number. That's right.

427
00:29:54,146 --> 00:29:55,773
I have a favor to ask.

428
00:29:56,273 --> 00:29:59,068
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

429
00:30:07,326 --> 00:30:08,577
Why isn't he here yet?

430
00:30:11,330 --> 00:30:13,457
Still no word from Ho-myeong?

431
00:30:13,541 --> 00:30:15,918
Ho-myeong isn't capable
of collecting that debt.

432
00:30:16,293 --> 00:30:18,421
He'll be lucky if he doesn't get beaten up
by those thugs.

433
00:30:25,469 --> 00:30:27,263
Hey, looks like they didn't beat you up
too badly.

434
00:30:27,346 --> 00:30:29,140
- Why weren't you answering your phone?
- What about the tab?

435
00:30:29,557 --> 00:30:30,558
Did you get it?

436
00:30:31,517 --> 00:30:32,810
I'm a little tired.

437
00:30:33,310 --> 00:30:34,687
I'm going to go upstairs and rest.

438
00:30:35,354 --> 00:30:36,355
Hey, wait.

439
00:30:43,320 --> 00:30:44,488
See? I told you.

440
00:30:44,572 --> 00:30:46,157
I told you it was
too much for him, didn't I?

441
00:30:51,579 --> 00:30:54,707
Jeez, if a man is going to
go out there with some grit

442
00:30:54,915 --> 00:30:57,042
he should at least come back with a few
bucks.

443
00:30:58,377 --> 00:31:01,046
Dad, you really don't know your
son-in-law at all, do you?

444
00:31:01,505 --> 00:31:04,383
From now on, absolutely no orders from
Heaven Capital.

445
00:31:04,550 --> 00:31:06,051
- Got it?
- Yeah, okay.

446
00:31:06,594 --> 00:31:07,595
Mister!

447
00:31:07,678 --> 00:31:08,804
- You got that?
- I got it.

448
00:31:20,691 --> 00:31:22,151
The more you rush,
the more careful you have to be.

449
00:31:23,152 --> 00:31:24,612
Have you already forgotten
what happened that day, ten years ago?

450
00:31:27,531 --> 00:31:29,366
You go to Yeongseon Island
and find Bulgae, okay?

451
00:31:29,450 --> 00:31:31,660
- Just find him.
- It's dangerous for you to go alone.

452
00:31:31,744 --> 00:31:33,037
- Let me go...
- No, don't come.

453
00:31:33,537 --> 00:31:36,040
Don't come and just lay low
until I contact you, all right?

454
00:31:36,123 --> 00:31:37,124
I'll be in touch.

455
00:31:59,939 --> 00:32:01,148
Han Gyeong-wook.

456
00:32:02,107 --> 00:32:03,859
Are you calling your superior by his name?

457
00:32:04,985 --> 00:32:06,237
Did you forget the chain of command?

458
00:32:07,655 --> 00:32:09,323
Han Gyeong-wook, you son of a bitch.

459
00:32:20,125 --> 00:32:22,836
So much for Team Leader Jo,
the champion of justice.

460
00:32:23,295 --> 00:32:25,839
Shaking in your boots
over a few measly bullets.

461
00:32:28,509 --> 00:32:29,969
I'll give you a chance to live.

462
00:32:30,553 --> 00:32:31,637
The location of the item...

463
00:32:32,096 --> 00:32:33,597
you guys know it, don't you?

464
00:32:34,098 --> 00:32:35,474
Did Jeong Ho-myeong come looking for it?

465
00:32:36,350 --> 00:32:37,393
Why?

466
00:32:40,354 --> 00:32:41,730
Even the great Han Gyeong-wook...

467
00:32:42,314 --> 00:32:43,315
is getting scared, I see.

468
00:32:46,277 --> 00:32:47,528
All right, fine.

469
00:32:47,611 --> 00:32:50,114
Well, if I get Jeong Ho-myeong here
and ask him myself

470
00:32:50,197 --> 00:32:51,448
I'm sure I'll get an answer.

471
00:32:51,532 --> 00:32:54,034
Yeah, good luck with that.

472
00:32:54,910 --> 00:32:57,746
You trained him,
so you know him best, right?

473
00:32:57,830 --> 00:32:59,540
Of course, I do.

474
00:32:59,623 --> 00:33:01,375
I know exactly what kind
of man Jeong Ho-myeong is.

475
00:33:02,751 --> 00:33:03,877
In terms of pure skill

476
00:33:03,961 --> 00:33:06,672
he's the best there is.

477
00:33:08,799 --> 00:33:10,968
But his weakness is
that he cares too much.

478
00:33:15,472 --> 00:33:18,934
Jeong Ho-myeong is fiercely l
oyal to his senior.

479
00:33:19,018 --> 00:33:20,978
If he hears that
Team Leader Jo Seong-won is dead

480
00:33:21,937 --> 00:33:23,147
he will show up

481
00:33:23,397 --> 00:33:25,357
at the funeral no matter what.

482
00:33:25,816 --> 00:33:26,817
Am I wrong?

483
00:33:36,327 --> 00:33:37,536
Looks like the counter-intelligence agents
have arrived.

484
00:33:38,329 --> 00:33:39,330
We should pull out now.

485
00:33:44,168 --> 00:33:45,252
Let's fall back for now.

486
00:33:45,336 --> 00:33:47,338
Post our agents
at all the places he might go.

487
00:33:47,713 --> 00:33:48,714
Understood.

488
00:33:54,678 --> 00:33:56,180
I won't lose him this time.

489
00:33:57,222 --> 00:33:58,223
Never.

490
00:33:58,932 --> 00:34:01,477
NIS AGENT MISSING... INTERNAL MANAGEMENT
FLAWS EXPOSED AT INTELLIGENCE AGENCY

491
00:34:14,281 --> 00:34:15,658
103BEO 8589

492
00:34:22,831 --> 00:34:25,918
- Yes, Chief Kim.
- I tailed the car like you asked.

493
00:34:26,001 --> 00:34:27,503
But do you really...

494
00:34:28,337 --> 00:34:29,380
need to know this?

495
00:34:29,463 --> 00:34:31,090
You couldn't track the owner's movements?

496
00:34:31,173 --> 00:34:32,299
No, that's not it.

497
00:34:32,383 --> 00:34:33,467
The owner of the car is...

498
00:34:36,178 --> 00:34:37,513
Han Gyeong-wook's secretary.

499
00:34:39,431 --> 00:34:40,474
Han Gyeong-wook?

500
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:42,643
Yes.

501
00:34:43,769 --> 00:34:46,105
Han Gyeong-wook, the one running
for Mayor of Imcheon.

502
00:34:49,858 --> 00:34:50,901
Prosecutor.

503
00:34:50,984 --> 00:34:52,277
You should just drop this case.

504
00:34:53,153 --> 00:34:55,698
You were only just transferred here

505
00:34:56,031 --> 00:34:59,118
and I'm worried you'll be
shipped out again just as fast.

506
00:34:59,702 --> 00:35:00,703
And besides, right now...

507
00:35:04,832 --> 00:35:06,166
HAN GYEONG-WOOK

508
00:35:13,048 --> 00:35:15,259
A SPECIAL TOURISM ZONE WILL
REVITALIZE YEONGSEON ISLAND

509
00:35:20,431 --> 00:35:21,890
Han Gyeong-wook!

510
00:35:21,974 --> 00:35:23,684
- Han Gyeong-wook!
- Han Gyeong-wook!

511
00:35:23,767 --> 00:35:25,394
-Han Gyeong-wook!
-Han Gyeong-wook!

512
00:35:25,477 --> 00:35:27,271
- Han Gyeong-wook!
- Han Gyeong-wook!

513
00:35:27,354 --> 00:35:29,022
- Han Gyeong-wook!
- Han Gyeong-wook!

514
00:35:29,106 --> 00:35:30,607
-Han Gyeong-wook!
-Han Gyeong-wook!

515
00:35:31,108 --> 00:35:32,568
-Han Gyeong-wook!
-Han Gyeong-wook!

516
00:35:32,985 --> 00:35:34,319
-Han Gyeong-wook!
-Han Gyeong-wook!

517
00:35:50,836 --> 00:35:52,963
I've identified the owner of the
motorcycle you mentioned yesterday.

518
00:35:53,213 --> 00:35:54,214
But the owner...

519
00:35:54,465 --> 00:35:57,509
is a high school student with no
connection to Bulgae or North Korea.

520
00:36:05,476 --> 00:36:07,227
I'm done. I'll get it.

521
00:36:10,731 --> 00:36:12,441
Where are you going?
You were in the middle of peeling onions.

522
00:36:16,403 --> 00:36:17,654
I'm going to go drum up some business.

523
00:36:17,738 --> 00:36:19,364
- We need to increase sales.
- All of a sudden?

524
00:36:19,448 --> 00:36:20,949
Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong!

525
00:36:21,325 --> 00:36:22,326
Hey!

526
00:36:29,875 --> 00:36:30,959
You little...

527
00:36:34,630 --> 00:36:35,964
We're just here to check something

528
00:36:36,048 --> 00:36:37,883
so let's not make this difficult for each
other.

529
00:36:38,217 --> 00:36:39,510
Make sure Chairman Do
doesn't hear about this.

530
00:36:39,593 --> 00:36:41,345
- You know what I mean?
- Yes.

531
00:36:42,304 --> 00:36:44,389
Kang-sik, give this kid
some money for medicine.

532
00:36:45,599 --> 00:36:47,768
Hurry up and find him. This isn't a game.

533
00:36:48,310 --> 00:36:50,103
- Boss!
- All right, Kang-sik found him.

534
00:36:50,479 --> 00:36:51,563
No, that's not it.

535
00:36:52,397 --> 00:36:53,398
Look at the lobby here.

536
00:36:54,775 --> 00:36:55,776
This guy.

537
00:36:56,109 --> 00:36:57,110
Isn't that Ma Gong-bok?

538
00:36:57,736 --> 00:36:58,737
Ma Gong-bok?

539
00:37:01,114 --> 00:37:02,991
Gong-bok showed up after ten years?

540
00:37:03,534 --> 00:37:04,827
On an island like this, of all places?

541
00:37:06,286 --> 00:37:07,538
Hey, Boss! We found him.

542
00:37:08,038 --> 00:37:09,039
It's that guy! That guy right there!

543
00:37:17,381 --> 00:37:18,674
Is this really him?

544
00:37:19,633 --> 00:37:21,510
He's so scrawny.
He looks like he couldn't hurt a fly.

545
00:37:22,219 --> 00:37:23,720
Oh, that's him all right, Boss.

546
00:37:27,599 --> 00:37:28,600
Hey, hey, hey!

547
00:37:30,894 --> 00:37:32,479
The guy who beat up my son

548
00:37:32,563 --> 00:37:34,565
and Gong-bok showed up on the same day?

549
00:37:42,531 --> 00:37:46,159
YEONGSEON POLICE SUBSTATION

550
00:37:48,120 --> 00:37:49,454
- Aren't you going on patrol?
- What?

551
00:37:50,455 --> 00:37:51,498
MY CASH COW

552
00:37:52,416 --> 00:37:54,209
You guys go on ahead.

553
00:38:03,886 --> 00:38:05,762
Yes, hello?

554
00:38:05,846 --> 00:38:07,514
Hey, Officer Kim, how have you been?

555
00:38:07,764 --> 00:38:09,600
I'm doing well, thanks to you.

556
00:38:09,933 --> 00:38:11,435
So, what can I do for you?

557
00:38:11,518 --> 00:38:14,396
A small problem came up
at one of my businesses

558
00:38:14,479 --> 00:38:15,981
and I need you to look into something.

559
00:38:16,273 --> 00:38:17,774
I'm going to send you a few pictures.

560
00:38:17,858 --> 00:38:19,484
I need you to track down these two guys.

561
00:38:19,568 --> 00:38:21,278
If you look through the footage
from the road

562
00:38:21,361 --> 00:38:23,238
near the Heaven Hotel
around 3 o'clock yesterday

563
00:38:23,322 --> 00:38:24,573
it shouldn't be hard
to trace their movements.

564
00:38:24,656 --> 00:38:27,075
Okay. Please send the pictures.

565
00:38:35,876 --> 00:38:37,127
MY CASH COW

566
00:38:40,881 --> 00:38:43,216
YEONGSEON STEEL

567
00:39:03,070 --> 00:39:04,154
Manager Bong.

568
00:39:04,529 --> 00:39:06,239
Why did you skip work
yesterday without notice?

569
00:39:06,990 --> 00:39:07,991
Manager Lee.

570
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,534
I'm so sorry.

571
00:39:10,327 --> 00:39:12,204
It must have been tough for you since I
was gone without a word, right?

572
00:39:14,623 --> 00:39:17,250
I covered for you and told the boss you
took a scheduled day off.

573
00:39:18,710 --> 00:39:20,379
- Manager Lee.
- There must be a reason

574
00:39:20,462 --> 00:39:22,130
why someone who's never done this before
would suddenly skip work.

575
00:39:23,799 --> 00:39:25,884
Thank you.
I'll be sure to repay you for this.

576
00:39:26,259 --> 00:39:27,260
But...

577
00:39:27,636 --> 00:39:29,262
why were you out yesterday?

578
00:39:29,763 --> 00:39:30,764
And your face...

579
00:39:33,058 --> 00:39:34,142
Well...

580
00:39:34,685 --> 00:39:36,311
Manager Lee, in your opinion

581
00:39:36,395 --> 00:39:38,772
what do you think I did
when I was younger?

582
00:39:39,439 --> 00:39:40,440
What you did?

583
00:39:46,530 --> 00:39:48,115
Didn't you work at a car wash?

584
00:39:48,198 --> 00:39:49,908
You're so good at washing cars.

585
00:39:49,992 --> 00:39:51,868
No, not that.

586
00:39:54,579 --> 00:39:55,747
Just take a good look.

587
00:39:56,581 --> 00:39:57,708
Does anything come to mind?

588
00:39:58,250 --> 00:40:01,211
Like a certain
vibe I give off or something.

589
00:40:03,630 --> 00:40:04,631
- One.
- Oh my.

590
00:40:07,426 --> 00:40:08,427
- Two.
- What...

591
00:40:11,304 --> 00:40:12,347
One.

592
00:40:15,851 --> 00:40:17,102
- Manager Bong.
- Two.

593
00:40:19,479 --> 00:40:20,939
- What are you doing?
- I wasn't doing anything.

594
00:40:21,023 --> 00:40:22,065
Are you crazy?

595
00:40:22,441 --> 00:40:23,525
I'm not crazy, but...

596
00:40:26,778 --> 00:40:27,863
Go wash the car.

597
00:40:28,447 --> 00:40:29,948
Since you didn't do it yesterday.
Make it spotless.

598
00:40:30,282 --> 00:40:31,283
Yes, sir.

599
00:40:46,631 --> 00:40:49,051
How dare you? Taking a day off
without my permission?

600
00:40:49,551 --> 00:40:51,887
Manager Bong. When you take a day off

601
00:40:52,054 --> 00:40:54,681
from now on,
you get my permission first. Got it?

602
00:41:13,492 --> 00:41:14,493
Smack!

603
00:41:19,998 --> 00:41:21,625
When the hero is in danger

604
00:41:21,708 --> 00:41:23,502
their past just suddenly
comes flashing back.

605
00:41:41,812 --> 00:41:43,021
Boss!

606
00:41:55,617 --> 00:41:57,702
Boss. I need to take a half day.

607
00:41:58,286 --> 00:41:59,663
You told me to ask first.

608
00:41:59,871 --> 00:42:01,123
So I'm telling you, I'm taking one.

609
00:42:04,292 --> 00:42:05,293
A half day.

610
00:42:07,462 --> 00:42:08,505
Fine, take it.

611
00:42:10,173 --> 00:42:11,174
A half day.

612
00:42:21,393 --> 00:42:22,686
Seriously? Is this it?

613
00:42:24,146 --> 00:42:25,647
We take bank transfers too.

614
00:42:27,607 --> 00:42:28,692
Answer carefully.

615
00:42:28,817 --> 00:42:30,026
Excuse me, fellas.

616
00:42:32,737 --> 00:42:33,989
Can I ask you guys something?

617
00:42:34,072 --> 00:42:35,866
What is it? I'm busy. Can't you see?

618
00:42:36,116 --> 00:42:37,325
You don't look that busy.

619
00:42:38,326 --> 00:42:39,911
Enough with the tough-guy act.

620
00:42:39,995 --> 00:42:41,580
Just answer my question.

621
00:42:42,038 --> 00:42:44,291
Which one of you is Kim Jin-su?

622
00:42:48,420 --> 00:42:49,421
That's me.

623
00:42:54,718 --> 00:42:55,927
Kim Jin-su.

624
00:42:58,680 --> 00:43:01,057
This isn't the guy I saw
on the motorcycle.

625
00:43:02,893 --> 00:43:04,394
So you're Jin-su.

626
00:43:05,437 --> 00:43:06,813
- Jin-su.
- Yeah?

627
00:43:07,564 --> 00:43:08,815
You own a motorcycle, right?

628
00:43:09,024 --> 00:43:10,442
Did you happen to lend
that motorcycle to anyone?

629
00:43:10,525 --> 00:43:11,735
And why should I tell you?

630
00:43:11,860 --> 00:43:12,986
Could you please tell me?

631
00:43:13,069 --> 00:43:14,613
It's really important that I find out.

632
00:43:14,738 --> 00:43:16,698
If it's that important to you

633
00:43:16,990 --> 00:43:18,200
then you should offer something for it.

634
00:43:18,533 --> 00:43:19,534
You expect it for free?

635
00:43:22,078 --> 00:43:23,079
Hold him.

636
00:43:27,209 --> 00:43:29,169
All right, let's see what you've got.

637
00:43:29,252 --> 00:43:31,087
If I like what I see, I'll tell you.

638
00:43:31,421 --> 00:43:34,466
Jeez, what should I do?
I don't have any money

639
00:43:35,008 --> 00:43:36,509
but I can give you something else.

640
00:43:45,936 --> 00:43:47,312
- Jin-su.
- Hey.

641
00:43:50,398 --> 00:43:52,484
Hey, what are you doing? Get him! Hurry!

642
00:43:52,817 --> 00:43:53,818
You!

643
00:44:11,711 --> 00:44:13,546
When an adult asks you a question

644
00:44:13,838 --> 00:44:16,716
you answer. Where are your manners?

645
00:44:17,550 --> 00:44:21,137
- Trying to throw a punch at me?
- Sir! Sir!

646
00:44:21,221 --> 00:44:22,847
It hurts!

647
00:44:28,895 --> 00:44:30,146
- Jin-su.
- Yes.

648
00:44:30,855 --> 00:44:33,024
- I'm going to ask you one more time.
- Yes.

649
00:44:33,358 --> 00:44:34,734
You own a motorcycle, right?

650
00:44:34,818 --> 00:44:35,902
That shiny one.

651
00:44:36,111 --> 00:44:37,988
- You mean my Scooter?
- Yes, that's the one. Your Scooter.

652
00:44:39,656 --> 00:44:41,157
That punk Heo Nam-il took it.

653
00:44:41,491 --> 00:44:42,492
Why?

654
00:44:42,951 --> 00:44:44,119
- Heo Nam-il?
- Yes.

655
00:44:48,081 --> 00:44:50,125
Is this guy trying to
drive me into the ground?

656
00:44:56,131 --> 00:44:57,716
Orthostatic hypotension...

657
00:45:19,195 --> 00:45:20,196
Are you all right?

658
00:45:22,073 --> 00:45:23,074
I'm sorry.

659
00:45:25,869 --> 00:45:27,287
When did you get here?

660
00:45:28,747 --> 00:45:29,956
Just now.

661
00:45:31,207 --> 00:45:32,876
- But are you not feeling well?
- No, it's just...

662
00:45:33,043 --> 00:45:34,044
Well...

663
00:45:34,127 --> 00:45:35,587
I just...

664
00:45:36,004 --> 00:45:37,505
haven't been sleeping well lately.

665
00:45:38,465 --> 00:45:39,466
I'm sorry.

666
00:45:48,558 --> 00:45:49,934
Do you have the lunch box there?

667
00:45:50,018 --> 00:45:51,227
Lunch box? Oh, yes.

668
00:45:51,311 --> 00:45:52,520
Just a moment.

669
00:46:02,113 --> 00:46:03,490
- It's fried chicken with sweet sauce.
- Yes.

670
00:46:14,000 --> 00:46:15,335
Oh, please...

671
00:46:16,127 --> 00:46:18,254
don't feel obligated.

672
00:46:18,588 --> 00:46:22,050
Luckily what you mentioned was available

673
00:46:22,133 --> 00:46:23,385
so I decided to order it.

674
00:46:24,344 --> 00:46:25,512
It's...

675
00:46:26,388 --> 00:46:28,306
It's what we do for our regulars.

676
00:46:32,811 --> 00:46:34,270
You said you weren't sleeping well, right?

677
00:46:36,272 --> 00:46:37,899
Can you hold out your hand for me?

678
00:46:43,279 --> 00:46:45,073
This is how you do it for handcuffs.

679
00:46:45,573 --> 00:46:46,825
My arm's a bit numb.

680
00:46:48,159 --> 00:46:49,160
No, like this.

681
00:46:49,411 --> 00:46:50,412
Like this.

682
00:46:55,792 --> 00:46:59,212
This is what I have
when I'm on my night rounds

683
00:47:00,046 --> 00:47:01,840
and it works pretty well.

684
00:47:03,466 --> 00:47:05,427
Have some. It'll help you wake up.

685
00:47:06,177 --> 00:47:07,178
Okay.

686
00:47:10,306 --> 00:47:11,307
Thank you.

687
00:47:11,975 --> 00:47:13,017
Thank you, too.

688
00:47:19,023 --> 00:47:20,024
Goodbye.

689
00:47:21,192 --> 00:47:22,235
Bye.

690
00:47:23,445 --> 00:47:24,446
Take care.

691
00:47:51,973 --> 00:47:53,183
She said thanks.

692
00:48:05,778 --> 00:48:06,779
What?

693
00:48:14,746 --> 00:48:17,665
You said you couldn't sleep
and felt like you were dying

694
00:48:17,749 --> 00:48:19,626
so I dropped everything and rushed over.

695
00:48:19,959 --> 00:48:22,337
- You look just fine.
- Can't you see these dark circles?

696
00:48:22,837 --> 00:48:24,130
Forget it. You should go home.

697
00:48:25,131 --> 00:48:26,549
You must be exhausted
for all sorts of reasons.

698
00:48:26,633 --> 00:48:28,593
Who's the one who ditched work

699
00:48:28,676 --> 00:48:29,802
and ran off in the first place?

700
00:48:31,012 --> 00:48:32,680
Did I go out and mess around like you did?

701
00:48:33,598 --> 00:48:35,391
Our business that you don't care about

702
00:48:35,475 --> 00:48:36,851
our real business!

703
00:48:37,852 --> 00:48:40,730
I was doing that while you were
goofing off with that woman!

704
00:48:41,022 --> 00:48:42,732
You little punk.

705
00:48:49,364 --> 00:48:50,365
Go ahead.

706
00:48:50,740 --> 00:48:51,741
Hit me.

707
00:48:52,784 --> 00:48:55,161
I'd love to take a good punch for a
change. Go on, hit me.

708
00:48:55,995 --> 00:48:56,996
Hit me.

709
00:49:03,378 --> 00:49:05,547
Let's cool off and talk about this later.

710
00:49:09,050 --> 00:49:10,468
You can't even hit me anymore?

711
00:49:12,637 --> 00:49:13,763
You know...

712
00:49:14,556 --> 00:49:16,891
I don't care about Gang Beom-ryong,
the owner of the Kind Convenience Store.

713
00:49:16,975 --> 00:49:19,227
I miss my old reckless boss

714
00:49:20,395 --> 00:49:22,564
Gang Beom-ryong from the Hwasan Sect.

715
00:49:23,064 --> 00:49:24,148
It's not working. Damn it.

716
00:49:44,252 --> 00:49:47,130
Gong-bok and Beom-ryong.
Those bastards show up after ten years

717
00:49:47,213 --> 00:49:48,631
and screw up my business?

718
00:49:50,091 --> 00:49:51,384
I should've just
finished them off back then.

719
00:49:54,637 --> 00:49:55,638
But, Boss...

720
00:49:56,180 --> 00:49:58,016
The guy who did this to us...

721
00:49:58,224 --> 00:50:01,728
do you really think he's connected to
Beom-ryong and Gong-bok?

722
00:50:02,061 --> 00:50:04,480
How dare you still
call his name so nicely?

723
00:50:05,898 --> 00:50:07,150
Look.

724
00:50:07,817 --> 00:50:09,402
Do you think it's a coincidence
that Gong-bok was there

725
00:50:09,485 --> 00:50:11,195
while you were getting beaten up?

726
00:50:12,238 --> 00:50:14,324
That bastard Gang Beom-ryong got rid of
Chairman Hwang Hwa-san

727
00:50:14,407 --> 00:50:15,950
to take his place, and now he's after me.

728
00:50:16,117 --> 00:50:18,202
He must've hired
some martial arts master or something.

729
00:50:19,662 --> 00:50:22,290
He can't fight me one-on-one like before,
so he pulls this kind of crap.

730
00:50:26,794 --> 00:50:30,798
This scar aches whenever it rains. I think
it's time for revenge.

731
00:50:31,674 --> 00:50:33,760
Boss, we heard from Sergeant Kim.

732
00:50:34,010 --> 00:50:35,928
-They've located both of them.
-Okay.

733
00:50:36,429 --> 00:50:38,139
- Everyone, get ready.
- Yes, Boss.

734
00:50:43,853 --> 00:50:45,021
Let's go!

735
00:50:45,104 --> 00:50:46,397
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

736
00:50:50,902 --> 00:50:51,903
So...

737
00:50:53,738 --> 00:50:56,407
- you got hit and your memory came back?
- No, before I got hit.

738
00:50:56,908 --> 00:50:59,285
I felt the baseball coming at me
from behind, and suddenly

739
00:50:59,369 --> 00:51:01,829
this scene just flashed through my mind.

740
00:51:03,456 --> 00:51:04,707
When I was younger...

741
00:51:05,833 --> 00:51:07,669
I had a six-pack

742
00:51:08,670 --> 00:51:09,962
and I kicked a dagger

743
00:51:10,046 --> 00:51:11,923
flying at me from behind!

744
00:51:12,632 --> 00:51:14,884
- You kicked a dagger? Come on.
- I'm serious!

745
00:51:15,468 --> 00:51:17,220
Try to hit me. Come on.

746
00:51:19,972 --> 00:51:20,973
Okay.

747
00:51:21,974 --> 00:51:23,351
I'll feel it coming and dodge.

748
00:51:34,487 --> 00:51:35,988
- Boss...
- Are they here?

749
00:51:36,072 --> 00:51:38,116
- Yes, they're here.
- Get in there, quickly!

750
00:51:38,199 --> 00:51:39,200
What the...

751
00:51:41,828 --> 00:51:43,329
So you little rats

752
00:51:43,413 --> 00:51:44,831
were hiding here, huh?

753
00:51:45,623 --> 00:51:46,958
What's this? Are you bowing to me?

754
00:51:53,297 --> 00:51:54,590
Hey, what's going on?

755
00:51:54,674 --> 00:51:55,675
What's this?

756
00:51:55,758 --> 00:51:57,009
What's going on?

757
00:51:57,343 --> 00:51:58,720
Hold on, it's not that.

758
00:51:58,803 --> 00:51:59,804
Wait a minute.

759
00:52:00,805 --> 00:52:02,432
What's going on?

760
00:52:02,515 --> 00:52:04,726
Did they know we were
coming or something? Damn it.

761
00:52:08,688 --> 00:52:09,689
Hey, hold on.

762
00:52:11,441 --> 00:52:12,859
Hold on.

763
00:52:20,450 --> 00:52:22,452
Damn, you scared me! Hey, get him!

764
00:52:22,785 --> 00:52:23,911
Hey, get that bastard!

765
00:52:24,287 --> 00:52:25,538
Jeez, you scared me.

766
00:52:35,089 --> 00:52:36,549
Welcome to Jumbo Convenience Store.

767
00:52:54,400 --> 00:52:55,610
Long time no see, Gong-bok.

768
00:53:15,797 --> 00:53:17,673
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

769
00:53:35,191 --> 00:53:36,859
Your food delivery is here.

770
00:53:39,028 --> 00:53:40,238
I'm coming in.

771
00:54:15,022 --> 00:54:16,649
The place is a mess.

772
00:54:16,732 --> 00:54:19,318
Someone might've beaten me to it.

773
00:54:23,614 --> 00:54:25,575
Yeongseon Steel.

774
00:54:29,745 --> 00:54:31,497
YEONGSEON FOOD

775
00:54:31,581 --> 00:54:32,874
Yeongseon...

776
00:54:33,583 --> 00:54:34,584
Food.

777
00:54:45,303 --> 00:54:46,554
You know...

778
00:54:46,637 --> 00:54:49,015
I don't care about Gang Beom-ryong,
the owner of the Kind Convenience Store.

779
00:54:49,390 --> 00:54:51,809
I miss my old reckless boss

780
00:54:52,810 --> 00:54:55,271
Gang Beom-ryong from the Hwasan Sect.

781
00:55:01,068 --> 00:55:02,320
Damn it.

782
00:55:13,998 --> 00:55:15,291
MA GONG-BOK

783
00:55:21,589 --> 00:55:24,008
MA GONG-BOK

784
00:55:25,301 --> 00:55:26,510
Hey, Gong-bok?

785
00:55:26,594 --> 00:55:28,888
Well, Beom-ryong, it's been a while.

786
00:55:29,889 --> 00:55:32,391
- Who is this?
- You don't recognize my voice?

787
00:55:32,642 --> 00:55:33,976
Come on, that hurts.

788
00:55:34,268 --> 00:55:35,269
It's me. In-gu.

789
00:55:37,980 --> 00:55:40,274
- How could you...
- We old Hwasan Sect guys

790
00:55:40,608 --> 00:55:41,817
should get together and catch up.

791
00:55:42,610 --> 00:55:44,445
I'll text you the location.

792
00:55:44,820 --> 00:55:46,489
Don't be late.

793
00:55:46,822 --> 00:55:48,741
I'm dying to see you.

794
00:55:48,824 --> 00:55:51,535
Boss, Beom-ryong, please help me.

795
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:00,920
DON'T MAKE ME ANY ANGRIER

796
00:56:45,589 --> 00:56:47,383
Now I'm sure of it.

797
00:56:48,050 --> 00:56:49,427
The man who was in this house...

798
00:56:56,851 --> 00:56:58,102
is the missing Bulgae.

799
00:56:59,395 --> 00:57:02,148
Come on. I'm not asking
for anything difficult.

800
00:57:02,773 --> 00:57:04,567
I just asked you to find someone

801
00:57:04,650 --> 00:57:06,569
who worked with Han Gyeong-wook.

802
00:57:06,652 --> 00:57:07,653
Is that really so difficult?

803
00:57:07,737 --> 00:57:09,196
Do you want to get someone fired?

804
00:57:09,405 --> 00:57:11,991
Han Gyeong-wook used to work here.

805
00:57:12,116 --> 00:57:14,368
Do you have any idea how many connections
he still has in this company?

806
00:57:14,493 --> 00:57:16,245
He quit to get into politics.

807
00:57:16,328 --> 00:57:17,830
I'm sure those connections are long gone.

808
00:57:17,913 --> 00:57:19,331
They're still as strong as ever.

809
00:57:19,415 --> 00:57:20,416
Look, I'm hanging up.

810
00:57:20,583 --> 00:57:22,043
Don't drag me into your mess.

811
00:57:22,126 --> 00:57:23,961
No, wait. Just one more question. That's
it.

812
00:57:24,253 --> 00:57:26,881
- Just one more question.
- Get up, you hear me?

813
00:57:27,256 --> 00:57:28,257
This son of a bitch.

814
00:57:28,424 --> 00:57:30,092
Who the hell is this guy?

815
00:57:34,472 --> 00:57:36,640
Jeez, just tell us already.

816
00:57:38,017 --> 00:57:39,226
Hey. Who do you work for?

817
00:57:40,102 --> 00:57:41,896
I'm just his uncle.

818
00:57:42,938 --> 00:57:44,565
So you're not going to talk, huh?

819
00:57:45,900 --> 00:57:47,276
Well, you leave me no choice.

820
00:57:47,359 --> 00:57:49,111
I'm going to ask you some questions.

821
00:57:50,154 --> 00:57:51,614
And if I don't like your answers

822
00:57:51,697 --> 00:57:53,199
or you piss me off...

823
00:57:53,282 --> 00:57:54,784
you'll get the bat.

824
00:57:55,451 --> 00:57:57,036
So think carefully before you answer.

825
00:57:59,413 --> 00:58:00,581
You son of a bitch.

826
00:58:01,916 --> 00:58:03,250
Let's start with you, Gong-bok.

827
00:58:05,086 --> 00:58:07,171
You bastard, why'd you suddenly show up?

828
00:58:07,338 --> 00:58:09,799
I was just minding my own business at the
convenience store.

829
00:58:10,257 --> 00:58:13,177
You're the one who showed up
out of nowhere, you bastard, Yoo In-gu.

830
00:58:13,260 --> 00:58:14,512
Has this bastard lost his mind?

831
00:58:16,222 --> 00:58:18,390
Gong-bok, let's think about this
logically.

832
00:58:18,808 --> 00:58:22,478
Right when I'm trying to start a new
business on Yeongseon Island...

833
00:58:23,187 --> 00:58:26,065
at my business, Heaven Capital, which
that bastard destroyed

834
00:58:26,482 --> 00:58:27,983
you showed up with him.

835
00:58:28,692 --> 00:58:31,153
And you're telling me you're just an
innocent convenience store clerk?

836
00:58:31,237 --> 00:58:32,488
Is this all just a coincidence?

837
00:58:33,239 --> 00:58:34,490
Does that make any sense to you?

838
00:58:34,573 --> 00:58:36,826
I don't know
anything about it, you bastard.

839
00:58:39,245 --> 00:58:40,663
That's not the answer I wanted.

840
00:58:41,247 --> 00:58:42,248
Hey, get him up.

841
00:58:44,625 --> 00:58:45,709
Hurry.

842
00:58:50,131 --> 00:58:51,340
Come on, get him up.

843
00:58:51,423 --> 00:58:52,675
This bastard.

844
00:58:53,926 --> 00:58:55,094
We've got a customer.

845
00:59:29,628 --> 00:59:30,629
TWO NATIONAL INTELLIGENCE SERVICE AGENTS
CAUGHT COLLUDING WITH NORTH KOREA...

846
00:59:30,713 --> 00:59:33,716
THE MURDER OF DIRECTOR KWON SOON-BOK
GANG LEADER HWANG HWA-SAN IMPLICATED

847
00:59:34,884 --> 00:59:36,177
Ten years ago...

848
00:59:36,594 --> 00:59:38,137
the National Intelligence Service agents

849
00:59:38,220 --> 00:59:40,806
and the spy on the passenger ferry?

850
00:59:41,682 --> 00:59:43,434
Yes, that's the one.

851
00:59:44,476 --> 00:59:45,936
Who was in charge of it?

852
00:59:47,396 --> 00:59:48,606
Deputy Chief Han Gyeong-wook.

853
00:59:48,689 --> 00:59:50,024
Han Gyeong-wook?

854
00:59:51,734 --> 00:59:53,360
Oh, Han Gyeong-wook...

855
00:59:53,611 --> 00:59:55,905
Around that same time...

856
00:59:56,238 --> 01:00:00,075
he also arrested the culprit in the
murder of Director Kwon Soon-bok.

857
01:00:00,159 --> 01:00:02,536
- So, could these two cases be connected?
- Hey.

858
01:00:02,828 --> 01:00:04,121
That's all I can say.

859
01:00:04,663 --> 01:00:06,916
This case is classified.
It's orders from the top.

860
01:00:08,334 --> 01:00:10,461
This isn't like the other cases
you've handled.

861
01:00:10,836 --> 01:00:12,129
It's on a completely different level.

862
01:00:12,755 --> 01:00:14,506
Drop it now before you get hurt.

863
01:00:21,430 --> 01:00:22,848
Yes, Chief Kim.

864
01:00:24,308 --> 01:00:27,061
- What?
- He just suddenly crossed into my lane...

865
01:00:27,561 --> 01:00:30,189
- hit me, and just drove off.
- What about the other vehicle?

866
01:00:30,272 --> 01:00:32,274
I ran the plates...

867
01:00:32,733 --> 01:00:33,859
but it's a ghost car.

868
01:00:34,693 --> 01:00:35,945
A ghost car?

869
01:00:39,198 --> 01:00:41,659
Uncle. This is a dangerous situation.

870
01:00:41,742 --> 01:00:43,077
Do it already!

871
01:00:43,160 --> 01:00:44,536
Agent 007.

872
01:00:44,620 --> 01:00:46,372
I don't know! Just be quiet a minute.

873
01:00:50,292 --> 01:00:51,335
Just a second.

874
01:00:52,086 --> 01:00:53,462
Don't you have to get hit for it to work?

875
01:00:54,046 --> 01:00:55,047
Are you crazy?

876
01:00:55,130 --> 01:00:56,257
You're telling me to take a punch?

877
01:00:57,216 --> 01:00:58,801
- I'm still hurting from before.
- Hey!

878
01:00:59,385 --> 01:01:00,594
You two are next

879
01:01:00,678 --> 01:01:02,012
so keep your mouths shut.

880
01:01:10,271 --> 01:01:12,773
Man, this guy's tough.
He just won't break.

881
01:01:13,565 --> 01:01:16,235
You're dead when Beom-ryong gets here,
you son of a bitch.

882
01:01:16,318 --> 01:01:18,195
Yeah? But I looked into it

883
01:01:18,862 --> 01:01:21,615
and this Gang Beom-ryong has been a
convenience store owner for ten years.

884
01:01:22,199 --> 01:01:23,784
A guy who's done nothing but scan barcodes
for a decade...

885
01:01:24,660 --> 01:01:26,036
you think he's still got his old moves?

886
01:01:53,272 --> 01:01:55,065
All right, let's move
on to the next in line.

887
01:01:55,691 --> 01:01:56,942
Hey, Mr. Martial Arts Master.

888
01:01:58,944 --> 01:02:01,280
Did those guys hire you
to beat my son to a pulp?

889
01:02:01,363 --> 01:02:02,823
Wait, sir.

890
01:02:02,906 --> 01:02:04,700
Hired? No, I'm just...

891
01:02:05,034 --> 01:02:06,827
an ordinary office worker.

892
01:02:06,910 --> 01:02:08,412
Just a regular salaryman.

893
01:02:08,871 --> 01:02:10,873
He's not a Martial Arts Master,
he's a comedian.

894
01:02:11,457 --> 01:02:12,541
You're sure he's the one who beat you?

895
01:02:12,624 --> 01:02:13,751
Yes, boss, I'm telling you.

896
01:02:14,084 --> 01:02:16,086
He took one hit and passed out, but then

897
01:02:16,462 --> 01:02:18,464
he slowly got up like a zombie

898
01:02:18,672 --> 01:02:21,133
rolled his eyes back,
and went totally berserk. I swear.

899
01:02:23,135 --> 01:02:24,261
Um, excuse me.

900
01:02:26,013 --> 01:02:27,139
Go on and hit him.

901
01:02:28,932 --> 01:02:30,934
- Go on, just hit him once!
- Are you insane?

902
01:02:31,018 --> 01:02:32,478
What is he, the Hulk?
He transforms when you hit him?

903
01:02:32,561 --> 01:02:34,271
No! Sir, it's not like that.

904
01:02:34,438 --> 01:02:35,689
Are you out of your mind?

905
01:02:35,981 --> 01:02:38,025
- It's okay, trust me.
- Look at these two, having fun.

906
01:02:38,609 --> 01:02:39,610
Hey, go ahead and hit him.

907
01:02:42,279 --> 01:02:43,530
Are you sure this is okay?

908
01:02:43,614 --> 01:02:45,449
- Should I do it?
- No. I'll do it.

909
01:02:51,497 --> 01:02:52,623
What the hell?

910
01:02:53,040 --> 01:02:54,458
Don't get smart with me! Dammit!

911
01:02:54,541 --> 01:02:57,252
Hey, you idiot! Is that the best you can
do? Hit him harder!

912
01:02:57,336 --> 01:02:58,337
That was plenty hard...

913
01:03:01,382 --> 01:03:02,383
Uncle!

914
01:03:09,890 --> 01:03:11,141
- Uncle!
- Look.

915
01:03:11,558 --> 01:03:12,559
There it is!

916
01:03:14,478 --> 01:03:17,648
It hurts so much.

917
01:03:19,650 --> 01:03:20,651
Uncle...

918
01:03:23,362 --> 01:03:24,363
Uncle!

919
01:03:27,074 --> 01:03:28,450
It hurts so much.

920
01:03:28,534 --> 01:03:31,370
I keep telling you, I'm
just a regular office worker.

921
01:03:32,413 --> 01:03:33,914
Hey! Stomp him!

922
01:03:34,331 --> 01:03:35,582
Hey, wait!

923
01:04:02,860 --> 01:04:04,027
Hey, Ma Gong-bok

924
01:04:04,111 --> 01:04:06,780
did your precious
convenience store boss run off?

925
01:04:06,864 --> 01:04:08,615
Why isn't he showing up, huh?

926
01:04:09,491 --> 01:04:11,743
He's supposed to be getting
revenge for this scar.

927
01:04:20,210 --> 01:04:21,336
I guess there's no choice.

928
01:04:22,504 --> 01:04:23,589
You'll have to be the next best thing.

929
01:04:24,298 --> 01:04:25,966
So I guess I'll have to
take it out on you.

930
01:04:43,942 --> 01:04:44,943
What the hell?

931
01:05:30,197 --> 01:05:31,406
Boss!

932
01:05:34,660 --> 01:05:36,703
- Gang Beom-ryong, that bastard.
- You bastard.

933
01:05:38,247 --> 01:05:39,790
I haven't slept in two days

934
01:05:39,873 --> 01:05:41,208
and I'm freaking exhausted.

935
01:05:42,501 --> 01:05:43,544
Ma Gong-bok.

936
01:05:45,629 --> 01:05:47,714
Let's wrap this up quick and get out of
here.

937
01:05:58,100 --> 01:06:00,561
FIFTIES PROFESSIONALS

938
01:06:12,155 --> 01:06:13,991
Seriously, what do you think you're doing?

939
01:06:14,324 --> 01:06:15,659
You think I enjoyed living like this?

940
01:06:15,784 --> 01:06:18,328
This is all your fault, Jeong Ho-myeong.

941
01:06:18,537 --> 01:06:20,622
Hard-working citizens like yourself...

942
01:06:20,706 --> 01:06:22,583
that's who cops like me
are supposed to protect.

943
01:06:24,501 --> 01:06:26,753
No matter how pure it is

944
01:06:26,837 --> 01:06:28,964
it only takes a few storms
to turn the water muddy...

945
01:06:29,339 --> 01:06:31,717
- It happens in an instant.
- I don't understand. Why?

946
01:06:31,925 --> 01:06:33,760
Something's definitely off.
This whole thing smells fishy.

947
01:06:34,344 --> 01:06:36,388
Be careful.
This is your first mission in ten years.

948
01:06:36,471 --> 01:06:38,181
Oh, come on!

949
01:06:38,265 --> 01:06:39,516
Have you forgotten who I am?

950
01:06:39,850 --> 01:06:41,310
Don't let his looks fool you.

951
01:06:41,393 --> 01:06:43,395
He's the top black ops agent
for the National Intelligence Service.

